title: Complete the square
text: Group and complete the square for $$x$$ and $$y$$ terms: $$4\left(x^2-2x\right)+9\left(y^2-8y\right)$$ and move constants.

title: Convert to standard form
text: After completing the square and dividing, you’ll get ((x-1)**2)/9​+((y-4)**2)/4​=1, which shows a horizontal major axis.
